<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Aubrey Moore's Blog (Posts about wingbeat)</title><link>https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/categories/wingbeat.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents Â© 2025 &lt;a href="mailto:aubreymoore2013@gmail.com"&gt;Aubrey Moore&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 16 Apr 2025 02:17:52 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Recording Insect Wingbeat Waveforms</title><link>https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/</link><dc:creator>Aubrey Moore</dc:creator><description>&lt;section id="making-the-sensor"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Making the sensor&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coming soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section id="recording-signals"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Recording signals&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;section id="hardware"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Hardware&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I record using a USB sound card (&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://www.amazon.com/Adapter-CableCreation-External-Windows-Drivers/dp/B01H2XF8V8?th=1)"&gt;Cable Creation USB Audio External Sound Card&lt;/a&gt;).
The sensor is plugged into the microphone jack of the USB device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section id="software"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Software&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I record using a Linux command line program called &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;arecord&lt;/code&gt;.
To find the right parameters for the USB sound card, I run the following command which creates a list of installed audio devices.
As you can see, it is recognized as card 2, device 0.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-1" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-1" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;$&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;arecord&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-l
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-2" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-2" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-3" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-3" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;List&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;of&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;CAPTURE&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Hardware&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Devices
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-4" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-4" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-4"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;card&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;PCH&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;HDA&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Intel&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;PCH&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;device&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;ALC1220&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Analog&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;ALC1220&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Analog&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-5" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-5" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Subdevices:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;/1
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-6" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-6" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-6"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Subdevice&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;#0: subdevice #0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-7" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-7" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-7"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;card&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Creation&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;Cable&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Creation&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;device&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;USB&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Audio&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;USB&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Audio&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-8" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-8" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-8"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Subdevices:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;/1
&lt;a id="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-9" name="rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-9" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_1dcdcc7ca6b7436e8f17ab500f2489d3-9"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Subdevice&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;#0: subdevice #0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can now record a 10 second audio file using the following command.
The parameters are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-D&lt;/span&gt; hw:2,0&lt;/code&gt;: the device to record from (card 2, device 0)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-d&lt;/span&gt; 10&lt;/code&gt;: the duration of the recording (10 seconds)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-f&lt;/span&gt; dat&lt;/code&gt;: the format of the recording (dat) (16 bit little endian, 48000 Hz)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-c&lt;/span&gt; 1&lt;/code&gt;: the number of channels (1 channel, mono)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-1" name="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-1" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;$&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;arecord&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-D&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;hw:2,0&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-d&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-f&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;dat&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-c&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;audio.wav
&lt;a id="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-2" name="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-2" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a id="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-3" name="rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-3" href="https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/#rest_code_eb91bc19ee8f479c972d53c92f5bc1e0-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Recording&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;WAVE&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;'audio.wav'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Signed&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;bit&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Little&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Endian,&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Rate&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;48000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Hz,&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Mono
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</description><category>wingbeat</category><guid>https://aubreymoore.github.io/blog2025/posts/recording-insect-wingbeat-waveforms/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 11 Apr 2025 09:14:51 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>